{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":841,"text":"So I know TED is about a lot\nof things that are big,"},{"time":4596,"text":"but I want to talk to you\nabout something very small."},{"time":8150,"text":"So small, it's a single word."},{"time":11093,"text":"The word is \"misfit.\""},{"time":13347,"text":"It's one of my favorite words,\nbecause it's so literal."},{"time":17403,"text":"I mean, it's a person\nwho sort of missed fitting in."},{"time":21752,"text":"Or a person who fits in badly."},{"time":24658,"text":"Or this: \"a person who is poorly adapted"},{"time":27605,"text":"to new situations and environments.\""},{"time":31298,"text":"I'm a card-carrying misfit."},{"time":34307,"text":"And I'm here for the other\nmisfits in the room,"},{"time":37164,"text":"because I'm never the only one."},{"time":39995,"text":"I'm going to tell you a misfit story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43237,"text":"Somewhere in my early 30s,"},{"time":45793,"text":"the dream of becoming a writer\ncame right to my doorstep."},{"time":50198,"text":"Actually, it came to my mailbox"},{"time":51826,"text":"in the form of a letter that said\nI'd won a giant literary prize"},{"time":55509,"text":"for a short story I had written."},{"time":58183,"text":"The short story was about my life\nas a competitive swimmer"},{"time":62632,"text":"and about my crappy home life,"},{"time":65258,"text":"and a little bit about how grief\nand loss can make you insane."},{"time":71829,"text":"The prize was a trip to New York City\nto meet big-time editors and agents"},{"time":76526,"text":"and other authors."},{"time":78278,"text":"So kind of it was the wannabe\nwriter's dream, right?"},{"time":82573,"text":"You know what I did the day\nthe letter came to my house?"},{"time":86037,"text":"Because I'm me,"},{"time":87859,"text":"I put the letter on my kitchen table,"},{"time":90080,"text":"I poured myself a giant glass of vodka"},{"time":93922,"text":"with ice and lime,"},{"time":96722,"text":"and I sat there in my underwear\nfor an entire day,"},{"time":100950,"text":"just staring at the letter."},{"time":104608,"text":"I was thinking about all the ways\nI'd already screwed my life up."},{"time":107777,"text":"Who the hell was I to go to New York City"},{"time":110975,"text":"and pretend to be a writer?"},{"time":113681,"text":"Who was I?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":115070,"text":"I'll tell you."},{"time":116745,"text":"I was a misfit."},{"time":118625,"text":"Like legions of other children,"},{"time":121908,"text":"I came from an abusive household"},{"time":124300,"text":"that I narrowly escaped with my life."},{"time":127727,"text":"I already had two epically\nfailed marriages underneath my belt."},{"time":132242,"text":"I'd flunked out of college\nnot once but twice"},{"time":135232,"text":"and maybe even a third time\nthat I'm not going to tell you about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138448,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":140582,"text":"And I'd done an episode\nof rehab for drug use."},{"time":144795,"text":"And I'd had two lovely\nstaycations in jail."},{"time":150228,"text":"So I'm on the right stage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":156744,"text":"But the real reason,\nI think, I was a misfit,"},{"time":160261,"text":"is that my daughter died\nthe day she was born,"},{"time":163547,"text":"and I hadn't figured out\nhow to live with that story yet."},{"time":168233,"text":"After my daughter died\nI also spent a long time homeless,"},{"time":173384,"text":"living under an overpass"},{"time":175352,"text":"in a kind of profound state\nof zombie grief and loss"},{"time":179594,"text":"that some of us encounter along the way."},{"time":182132,"text":"Maybe all of us, if you live long enough."},{"time":186240,"text":"You know, homeless people\nare some of our most heroic misfits,"},{"time":190261,"text":"because they start out as us."},{"time":194670,"text":"So you see, I'd missed fitting in\nto just about every category out there:"},{"time":200112,"text":"daughter, wife, mother, scholar."},{"time":205474,"text":"And the dream of being a writer"},{"time":207997,"text":"was really kind of like a small,\nsad stone in my throat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214906,"text":"It was pretty much in spite of myself\nthat I got on that plane"},{"time":218399,"text":"and flew to New York City,"},{"time":220810,"text":"where the writers are."},{"time":223168,"text":"Fellow misfits, I can almost\nsee your heads glowing."},{"time":226867,"text":"I can pick you out of a room."},{"time":228803,"text":"At first, you would've loved it."},{"time":231265,"text":"You got to choose the three\nfamous writers you wanted to meet,"},{"time":234241,"text":"and these guys went\nand found them for you."},{"time":236623,"text":"You got set up at the Gramercy Park Hotel,"},{"time":239437,"text":"where you got to drink Scotch\nlate in the night"},{"time":242095,"text":"with cool, smart, swank people."},{"time":244610,"text":"And you got to pretend you were cool\nand smart and swank, too."},{"time":249143,"text":"And you got to meet a bunch\nof editors and authors and agents"},{"time":252355,"text":"at very, very fancy lunches and dinners."},{"time":257377,"text":"Ask me how fancy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259735,"text":"Audience: How fancy?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":262077,"text":"Lidia Yuknavitch: I'm making a confession:\nI stole three linen napkins --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":266419,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":268014,"text":"from three different restaurants."},{"time":270430,"text":"And I shoved a menu down my pants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272720,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":274820,"text":"I just wanted some keepsakes\nso that when I got home,"},{"time":278550,"text":"I could believe it had really\nhappened to me."},{"time":281241,"text":"You know?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":283467,"text":"The three writers I wanted to meet"},{"time":285155,"text":"were Carole Maso, Lynne Tillman\nand Peggy Phelan."},{"time":288496,"text":"These were not famous,\nbest-selling authors,"},{"time":291574,"text":"but to me, they were women-writer titans."},{"time":295700,"text":"Carole Maso wrote the book\nthat later became my art bible."},{"time":300056,"text":"Lynne Tillman gave me\npermission to believe"},{"time":302581,"text":"that there was a chance\nmy stories could be part of the world."},{"time":306839,"text":"And Peggy Phelan reminded me"},{"time":308817,"text":"that maybe my brains\ncould be more important than my boobs."},{"time":315500,"text":"They weren't mainstream women writers,"},{"time":318208,"text":"but they were cutting a path\nthrough the mainstream"},{"time":322009,"text":"with their body stories,"},{"time":324294,"text":"I like to think, kind of the way\nwater cut the Grand Canyon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329371,"text":"It nearly killed me with joy"},{"time":331106,"text":"to hang out with these three\nover-50-year-old women writers."},{"time":334971,"text":"And the reason it nearly\nkilled me with joy"},{"time":337921,"text":"is that I'd never known a joy like that."},{"time":340014,"text":"I'd never been in a room like that."},{"time":342350,"text":"My mother never went to college."},{"time":344747,"text":"And my creative career to that point"},{"time":347260,"text":"was a sort of small, sad, stillborn thing."},{"time":353394,"text":"So kind of in those first nights\nin New York I wanted to die there."},{"time":356697,"text":"I was just like, \"Kill me now.\nI'm good. This is beautiful.\""},{"time":361187,"text":"Some of you in the room\nwill understand what happened next."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364935,"text":"First, they took me to the offices\nof Farrar, Straus and Giroux."},{"time":369863,"text":"Farrar, Straus and Giroux\nwas like my mega-dream press."},{"time":373062,"text":"I mean, T.S. Eliot and Flannery O'Connor\nwere published there."},{"time":377418,"text":"The main editor guy sat me down\nand talked to me for a long time,"},{"time":381817,"text":"trying to convince me I had a book in me"},{"time":384159,"text":"about my life as a swimmer."},{"time":386498,"text":"You know, like a memoir."},{"time":388630,"text":"The whole time he was talking to me,"},{"time":390890,"text":"I sat there smiling and nodding\nlike a numb idiot,"},{"time":395509,"text":"with my arms crossed over my chest,"},{"time":397385,"text":"while nothing, nothing, nothing\ncame out of my throat."},{"time":403875,"text":"So in the end, he patted me\non the shoulder"},{"time":407266,"text":"like a swim coach might."},{"time":409580,"text":"And he wished me luck"},{"time":411439,"text":"and he gave me some free books"},{"time":413901,"text":"and he showed me out the door."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417588,"text":"Next, they took me\nto the offices of W.W. Norton,"},{"time":420879,"text":"where I was pretty sure\nI'd be escorted from the building"},{"time":423603,"text":"just for wearing Doc Martens."},{"time":426190,"text":"But that didn't happen."},{"time":428512,"text":"Being at the Norton offices"},{"time":430965,"text":"felt like reaching up into the night sky\nand touching the moon"},{"time":435461,"text":"while the stars stitched your name\nacross the cosmos."},{"time":439599,"text":"I mean, that's how big\na deal it was to me."},{"time":441768,"text":"You get it?"},{"time":443567,"text":"Their lead editor, Carol Houck Smith,"},{"time":446089,"text":"leaned over right in my face\nwith these beady, bright, fierce eyes"},{"time":450456,"text":"and said, \"Well, send me\nsomething then, immediately!\""},{"time":454328,"text":"See, now most people,\nespecially TED people,"},{"time":456644,"text":"would have run to the mailbox, right?"},{"time":459651,"text":"It took me over a decade to even imagine"},{"time":462953,"text":"putting something in an envelope\nand licking a stamp."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468741,"text":"On the last night,"},{"time":470339,"text":"I gave a big reading\nat the National Poetry Club."},{"time":474342,"text":"And at the end of the reading,"},{"time":476313,"text":"Katharine Kidde of Kidde,\nHoyt &amp; Picard Literary Agency,"},{"time":480640,"text":"walked straight up to me and shook my hand"},{"time":483251,"text":"and offered me representation,\nlike, on the spot."},{"time":488558,"text":"I stood there and I kind of went deaf."},{"time":491569,"text":"Has this ever happened to you?"},{"time":493703,"text":"And I almost started crying"},{"time":495839,"text":"because all the people in the room\nwere dressed so beautifully,"},{"time":499788,"text":"and all that came out of my mouth was:"},{"time":502965,"text":"\"I don't know. I have to think about it.\""},{"time":506805,"text":"And she said, \"OK, then,\" and walked away."},{"time":512884,"text":"All those open hands out to me,\nthat small, sad stone in my throat ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519427,"text":"You see, I'm trying to tell you something\nabout people like me."},{"time":523389,"text":"Misfit people -- we don't always know\nhow to hope or say yes"},{"time":527466,"text":"or choose the big thing,"},{"time":529101,"text":"even when it's right in front of us."},{"time":531271,"text":"It's a shame we carry."},{"time":532914,"text":"It's the shame of wanting something good."},{"time":534929,"text":"It's the shame of feeling something good."},{"time":536945,"text":"It's the shame of not really believing\nwe deserve to be in the room"},{"time":541351,"text":"with the people we admire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544472,"text":"If I could, I'd go back\nand I'd coach myself."},{"time":547422,"text":"I'd be exactly like those\nover-50-year-old women who helped me."},{"time":551789,"text":"I'd teach myself how to want things,"},{"time":553714,"text":"how to stand up, how to ask for them."},{"time":556078,"text":"I'd say, \"You! Yeah, you!\nYou belong in the room, too.\""},{"time":560408,"text":"The radiance falls on all of us,"},{"time":562704,"text":"and we are nothing without each other."},{"time":567041,"text":"Instead, I flew back to Oregon,"},{"time":570337,"text":"and as I watched the evergreens\nand rain come back into view,"},{"time":576053,"text":"I just drank many tiny bottles\nof airplane \"feel sorry for yourself.\""},{"time":581491,"text":"I thought about how, if I was a writer,\nI was some kind of misfit writer."},{"time":587244,"text":"What I'm saying is,"},{"time":588427,"text":"I flew back to Oregon without a book deal,"},{"time":590455,"text":"without an agent,"},{"time":591630,"text":"and with only a headful\nand heart-ful of memories"},{"time":594139,"text":"of having sat so near"},{"time":597311,"text":"the beautiful writers."},{"time":600278,"text":"Memory was the only prize\nI allowed myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605175,"text":"And yet, at home in the dark,"},{"time":609272,"text":"back in my underwear,"},{"time":611788,"text":"I could still hear their voices."},{"time":614264,"text":"They said, \"Don't listen to anyone\nwho tries to get you to shut up"},{"time":618329,"text":"or change your story.\""},{"time":620861,"text":"They said, \"Give voice to the story\nonly you know how to tell.\""},{"time":624564,"text":"They said, \"Sometimes telling the story"},{"time":627018,"text":"is the thing that saves your life.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":631703,"text":"Now I am, as you can see,\nthe woman over 50."},{"time":636278,"text":"And I'm a writer."},{"time":638516,"text":"And I'm a mother."},{"time":640441,"text":"And I became a teacher."},{"time":642970,"text":"Guess who my favorite students are."},{"time":646604,"text":"Although it didn't happen the day"},{"time":648256,"text":"that dream letter came through my mailbox,"},{"time":650534,"text":"I did write a memoir,"},{"time":652231,"text":"called \"The Chronology of Water.\""},{"time":654889,"text":"In it are the stories of how many times\nI've had to reinvent a self"},{"time":659612,"text":"from the ruins of my choices,"},{"time":662575,"text":"the stories of how my seeming failures\nwere really just weird-ass portals"},{"time":668009,"text":"to something beautiful."},{"time":670309,"text":"All I had to do\nwas give voice to the story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675552,"text":"There's a myth in most cultures\nabout following your dreams."},{"time":680664,"text":"It's called the hero's journey."},{"time":683679,"text":"But I prefer a different myth,"},{"time":685527,"text":"that's slightly to the side of that"},{"time":687330,"text":"or underneath it."},{"time":689089,"text":"It's called the misfit's myth."},{"time":691763,"text":"And it goes like this:"},{"time":693623,"text":"even at the moment of your failure,"},{"time":695902,"text":"right then, you are beautiful."},{"time":699585,"text":"You don't know it yet,"},{"time":700761,"text":"but you have the ability\nto reinvent yourself"},{"time":703962,"text":"endlessly."},{"time":705184,"text":"That's your beauty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707694,"text":"You can be a drunk,"},{"time":709234,"text":"you can be a survivor of abuse,"},{"time":711607,"text":"you can be an ex-con,"},{"time":713067,"text":"you can be a homeless person,"},{"time":714589,"text":"you can lose all your money\nor your job or your husband"},{"time":717891,"text":"or your wife, or the worst thing of all,"},{"time":720329,"text":"a child."},{"time":721864,"text":"You can even lose your marbles."},{"time":723941,"text":"You can be standing dead center\nin the middle of your failure"},{"time":728034,"text":"and still, I'm only here to tell you,"},{"time":730936,"text":"you are so beautiful."},{"time":733073,"text":"Your story deserves to be heard,"},{"time":735396,"text":"because you, you rare\nand phenomenal misfit,"},{"time":739693,"text":"you new species,"},{"time":742568,"text":"are the only one in the room"},{"time":744561,"text":"who can tell the story"},{"time":746201,"text":"the way only you would."},{"time":749710,"text":"And I'd be listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752863,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754063,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}